For the first time since starting to follow #fungifriends I was in the right type of woods for finding shrooms and was inspired by photos from the feed to look for some of the teeny tiny ones that usually escape my eye. 

And I did find them! 
🍄 📷

images.alt: 4 little golden mushrooms poking out of a deadish tree. There’s moss up the left size of the tree. The shrooms are spaced far apart, except for one pair growing together.
A closer look at the pair of little golden shrooms growing out from a crack in a tree.
2 little mushrooms, one brown one almost white, growing out of a dead tree burl which is on the ground.
The littlest mushroom I found, this tiny white round mushroom with a very skinny stalk is growing amongst the grass and dead leaves of the forest floor.
